{{For|美國電視劇|山巔之城 (電視劇)}}
'''山上的城'''（City upon a hill）或'''山巔之城'''通常是指[[约翰·温斯罗普|约翰·温斯罗普]]于1630年在一次著名的[[布道|布道]]“基督徒慈善的典范”（A Model of Christian Charity）中提到的一个惯用语。當年温斯罗普購買了[[英國|英國]]新成立的馬薩諸塞公司的股票，舉家搬到[[馬薩諸塞|馬薩諸塞]]，溫索普本人則當選為殖民地總督，于1630年布道時他引用了马太福音5章14节[[耶穌|耶穌]]的[[登山宝训|登山宝训]]中关于[[盐和光|盐和光]]的隐喻：“你们是世上的光。城立在山上，是不能隐藏的。”来提醒在[[新英格兰|新英格兰]]建立[[馬薩諸塞灣殖民地|馬薩諸塞灣殖民地]]的[[清教徒|清教徒]]殖民者，他们的新社区将成为一座“山上的城”，被全球矚目：這成為新英格蘭殖民者放置在他們的山丘首府[[波士頓|波士頓]]的理想<ref>[http://history.hanover.edu/texts/winthmod.html  A Model of Christian Charity] {{Wayback|url=http://history.hanover.edu/texts/winthmod.html |date=19961208192250 }}—Governor John Winthrop (1630 on board the ''Arbella'')</ref>。清教徒新英格蘭社區將設置公共慈善事業，親情，團結的樣子走向世界，或者如果清教徒沒有維護他們與上帝的約，將受到神的審判。

== “基督徒慈善的典范”讲道 ==
{{cquote|我们必须认识到我们将成为一座山上的城。所有人的眼睛都在看着我们。因此如果我们在我们所作的这件事上对我们的上帝虚妄……我们将成为全世界的傳說和笑柄。我们将使敌人开口说毁谤上帝道路的话……我们将使上帝許多可敬的仆人臉面慚愧，使他們的禱告化成對我們的詛咒，直至我們離開正前往的美好土地。}}

<!-- It was long believed that the speech was given aboard the [[Arbella|Arbella]] not long before landing; recent research{{Fact|date=February 2007}} has shown, however, that it was almost certainly given in England prior to departure.  In any case, it inspired the Puritans with a sense of holy duty that would be crucial if they wanted to increase their chances of survival in the New World. --> 

温斯罗普相信所有民族都与上帝有契约。因为英格兰已经亵渎了这个宗教契约，所以清教徒必须离开这个国家。这表达了清教徒的一个信条——由于[[英國聖公會|英國聖公會]]接受[[天主教|天主教]]仪式，已经从恩典中堕落。<!--约翰·温斯罗普声称清教徒 forge a new, special agreement with God, like that between God and the people of [[Israel|Israel]]. However, unlike the Separatists (such as the [[Pilgrims|Pilgrims]]), the Puritans remained nominally a part of the Anglican church in hopes that it could be purified from within. Winthrop believed that by purifying Christianity in the New World, his followers would serve as an example to the Old World for building a model [[Protestant|Protestant]] community. -->
<!-- The idea that their community was specially ordained by God had a powerful effect on the Puritan society of New England. Of course, breaking a covenant with God has dire results (as [[Noah|Noah]]'s fellow men learned the hard way).  In order to avoid incurring God's wrath by breaking their promise, the Puritans sought to maintain perfect order in their society. Even the smallest sins were punished harshly by the courts; no one was allowed to live alone for fear that they would succumb to the temptation to sin; parents were to instruct their children and servants diligently in the Word of God; church attendance was mandatory; [[marriage|marriage]] was required. These conventions and institutions molded an extremely stable and well-structured society in New England, a stark contrast with the unstable and loosely-bound society of the early British colonies in the [[Chesapeake_Bay|Chesapeake Bay]] region, such as [[Jamestown,_Virginia|Jamestown]]. -->

== 美国政治中的引用 ==
這个比喻是[[美國例外論|美國例外論]]的早期例子，山上的城也已成為美國政客的流行語。

[[约翰·肯尼迪|约翰·肯尼迪]]在他就任美國總統前11天，在波士顿[[马萨诸塞州政府|马萨诸塞州政府]]的演说中，引用温斯罗普的著名的“山上的城”演说。在演说中，肯尼迪称，他希望他的政府拥有4个基本品质 ：勇气、判断、正直和奉献。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.jfklibrary.org/Historical+Resources/Archives/Reference+Desk/Speeches/JFK/ |title=Address of President-Elect John F. Kennedy Delivered to a Joint Convention of the General Court of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts |accessdate=2007-03-27 |archive-date=2007-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224002012/http://www.jfklibrary.org/Historical+Resources/Archives/Reference+Desk/Speeches/JFK/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

温斯罗普的演说还有一次著名的引用，是在1989年[[美国总统|美国总统]][[罗纳德·里根|罗纳德·里根]]辞别演说中<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reaganlibrary.gov/011189i|title=Farewell Address to the Nation {{!}} Ronald Reagan Presidential Library - National Archives and Records Administration|accessdate=2019-05-14|work=www.reaganlibrary.gov|archive-date=2019-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514101210/https://www.reaganlibrary.gov/011189i|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但是他强调了他自己对这个惯用语的解释。

